“A nice stroll buy snobby”
Dec 2020
I overheard someone talking about the beautiful Christmas decorations at the Aria, so we added it to our walkabout. We visited around 9:30 in the morning, before the shops were open. Apparently, since we weren't dressed in Burberry, Prada or Gucci, we didn't look like we belonged there. Immediately on entering we were approached by a security guard who told us none of the stores were open yet. I responded we just wanted to look around. I suppose we passed the test because he allowed us to proceed. Is IS all quite beautiful. But even if I was filthy, rotten, stinking rich, I wouldn't spend a dime in a place so snobby.

mwhamburger
Seattle, WA845 contributions
a free and permanent collection of amazing sculptures and art work at the Aria
Dec 2019
there is an awful lot to see and admire. Most memorable were: the Reclining Connected Forms outside the main lobby by Henry Moore, the Silver River by Maya Lin at the Registration desk, a creation entirely of cast and reclaimed silver of the Colorado River. Add to that the Big Edge by Nancy Rubins who sculpted hundreds of boats together at the Harmon Circle. Simply stunning.
At the Aria concierge desk you can get a map that shows you the way to all of the these attractions with pictures and text re. each artist.
Written December 19, 2019
